title: (x) Old userscripts.org logo - ITC American Typewriter {Viviane T}
content:
Any ideas what the font is in this old logotype for userscripts.org?

| Attachment | Size |
| --- | --- |
| [Userscripts.org](http://web.archive.org/web/20100108030410/http:/typophile.com/files/Screen%20shot%202010-01-06%20at%2010.20.21%20PM.png) | 9.02 KB |
author: jakedahn

comments.content: I was going to say [ITC American Typewriter bold](http://web.archive.org/web/20100108030410/http:/new.myfonts.com/fonts/agfa/itc-american-typewriter/), but all serifs seem to have sharper/cleaner edges in the logo.
